extends @views/layout/index.pug
include @views/mixins/code.pug

block variables
  - title = 'Runtime - Frontend tooling ecosystem';

append style
  link(rel='stylesheet' href='./style.scss')

block content
  section.section.m-b-4
    .container(data-animate='fade-down' data-animate-delay='200')
      h1.title-h1.m-b-2.text-gradient-deep.text-center Runtime
      p.title-h5.slate-500.text-center.m-b-2
        | Lightweight frontend runtime for SPA applications without frameworks
      p.title-h5.slate-500.text-center.m-b-4
        | Built for developers who want control without framework overhead
      .description
        p.m-b-1
          | The runtime provides a lightweight foundation for building modern single-page applications
          | without relying on large frontend frameworks.
          | It is designed around a modular architecture that separates concerns such as dependency injection,
          | routing, reactivity, and rendering into independent but cohesive parts.
        p.m-b-1
          | Developers can build fully functional applications using a minimal set of primitives
          | while maintaining full control over application structure and behavior.
          | The runtime includes a strict dependency injection system,
          | a client-side router with navigation guards, and a reactive state model powered by Proxy.
          | Components follow a predictable lifecycle, ensuring consistent initialization,
          | rendering, and cleanup across the application.
        p.m-b-1
          | Template bindings allow declarative DOM updates using simple data attributes,
          | reducing the need for manual DOM manipulation.
          | The runtime is framework-independent and has zero external dependencies,
          | making it suitable for long-term maintenance and custom architectures.
          | It integrates seamlessly with the build system and templates,
          | enabling a smooth development experience from project creation to deployment.
          | This approach allows you to build scalable applications with clear architecture,
          | without sacrificing performance or flexibility.

  section.section.m-b-4
    .container(data-animate='fade-up' data-animate-delay='200')
      h2.title-h2.m-b-4 Quick Start
      .card
        +code('ts', 'Bootstrap', true)
          | import { bootstrapApplication, provideRouter } from '@razerspine/runtime';
          |
          | bootstrapApplication({
          |   providers: [
          |     provideRouter([
          |       { path: '/', component: HomePage }
          |     ])
          |   ]
          | });

  section.section.m-b-4
    .container
      h2.title-h2.m-b-4 Core Features
      .row.row--gap-25
        .col-12.col-md-6
          .card(data-animate='fade-right' data-animate-delay='100')
            h3.title-h4.text-gradient-soft.m-b-2 DI Container
            p Strict dependency injection system

        .col-12.col-md-6
          .card(data-animate='fade-left' data-animate-delay='200')
            h3.title-h4.text-gradient-soft.m-b-2 Router
            p SPA navigation with guards

        .col-12.col-md-6
          .card(data-animate='fade-right' data-animate-delay='300')
            h3.title-h4.text-gradient-soft.m-b-2 Reactivity
            p Proxy-based reactive state

        .col-12.col-md-6
          .card(data-animate='fade-left' data-animate-delay='400')
            h3.title-h4.text-gradient-soft.m-b-2 Components
            p Lifecycle-driven architecture

  section.section.m-b-4
    .container(data-animate='fade-up' data-animate-delay='200')
      h2.title-h2.m-b-4 Component Example
      .card
        +code('ts', 'Component', true)
          | export class HomePage extends BaseComponent {
          |   increment() {
          |     this.setState({ count: this.state.count + 1 });
          |   }
          | }

  section.section.m-b-4
    .container(data-animate='fade-down' data-animate-delay='200')
      h2.title-h2.m-b-4 Architecture
      .card
        +code('text', 'Modules', false)
          | core → router → reactivity → view → http → platform

  section.section.m-b-4
    .container
      h2.title-h2.m-b-4(data-animate='fade-up') Common Mistakes & Anti-patterns
      p.title-h5.m-b-4(data-animate='fade-up' data-animate-delay='100')
        | Common pitfalls when working with the runtime and how to avoid them
      .card.m-b-4(data-animate='fade-up' data-animate-delay='200')
        +code('text', 'DI Container', false)
          | ❌ Injecting service without registering it
          | ✔ Always provide services in bootstrapApplication()
          |
          | ❌ Expecting automatic instantiation
          | ✔ Runtime uses strict DI mode (no auto new)
          |
          | ❌ Circular dependencies between services
          | ✔ Keep services isolated and avoid cross-dependency loops

      p.description.m-b-4(data-animate='fade-up' data-animate-delay='250')
        | The DI container works in strict mode. Services are not auto-created and must be explicitly
        | registered during bootstrap. If a service is missing, the runtime will throw an error
        | instead of silently failing, making configuration issues easier to detect.

      .card.m-b-4(data-animate='fade-up' data-animate-delay='300')
        +code('text', 'State Management', false)
          | ❌ Direct state mutation outside of setState
          | ✔ Always use setState() for predictable updates
          |
          | ❌ Replacing state object entirely
          | ✔ State is Proxy-based and must remain stable
          |
          | ❌ Mutating deeply without understanding reactivity
          | ✔ Use structured updates to keep UI in sync

      p.description.m-b-4(data-animate='fade-up' data-animate-delay='350')
        | The reactive system is based on Proxy. Direct mutation may work, but breaks predictable
        | update flow. setState() ensures controlled updates and keeps rendering consistent.

      .card.m-b-4(data-animate='fade-up' data-animate-delay='400')
        +code('text', 'Component Lifecycle', false)
          | ❌ Performing async logic inside render()
          | ✔ Use onInit() for async operations
          |
          | ❌ Forgetting cleanup for manual subscriptions
          | ✔ Use onDestroy() for cleanup
          |
          | ❌ Manipulating DOM outside render()
          | ✔ Let bindings handle DOM updates

      p.description.m-b-4(data-animate='fade-up' data-animate-delay='450')
        | The lifecycle is strictly ordered: render → bind events → update → onInit.
        | Async logic should be placed in onInit() to avoid inconsistent rendering behavior.

      .card.m-b-4(data-animate='fade-up' data-animate-delay='500')
        +code('text', 'Router', false)
          | ❌ Calling Router before bootstrap completes
          | ✔ Router is initialized inside bootstrapApplication
          |
          | ❌ Ignoring guard return types
          | ✔ Guards must return true | false | redirect string
          |
          | ❌ Assuming navigation errors will crash app
          | ✔ Router handles errors internally

      p.description.m-b-4(data-animate='fade-up' data-animate-delay='550')
        | The Router is designed to be fault-tolerant. Navigation errors are caught internally
        | and do not break the application lifecycle. Optional error handlers can be attached
        | for custom UI behavior.

      .card.m-b-4(data-animate='fade-up' data-animate-delay='600')
        +code('text', 'MPA Mode', false)
          | ❌ Forgetting to call applyBindings()
          | ✔ Must be called manually after state updates
          |
          | ❌ Using bindForms without applyBindings
          | ✔ They work together as a pair
          |
          | ❌ Not cleaning up listeners
          | ✔ Always remove listeners to avoid memory leaks

      p.description.m-b-4(data-animate='fade-up' data-animate-delay='650')
        | In MPA mode, lifecycle is fully manual. You must initialize bindings,
        | attach event handlers and handle cleanup yourself. Forgetting cleanup
        | may lead to memory leaks or duplicated listeners.

      .card.m-b-4(data-animate='fade-up' data-animate-delay='700')
        +code('text', 'Bindings Engine', false)
          | ❌ Relying on incorrect processing order
          | ✔ data-for always runs before other bindings
          |
          | ❌ Mixing manual DOM updates with bindings
          | ✔ Let applyBindings control DOM synchronization
          |
          | ❌ Misusing data-model on unsupported elements
          | ✔ Use proper input types for two-way binding

      p.description(data-animate='fade-up' data-animate-delay='750')
        | The bindings engine processes directives in a strict order. Structural changes like
        | data-for must be applied first to ensure correct DOM updates. Mixing manual DOM
        | manipulation with bindings may lead to inconsistent UI state.
